{"type":"message","id":"f9b47088","parentId":"441174be","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:23:40.937Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dc1zg5qul0jz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 082215\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. **Recent activity**: Just applied research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\r\n2. **Current focus**: Phase 1 - Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) experiment\r\n3. **Next action needed**: Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC experiment requires:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I should take ONE concrete action that advances the TIC experiment. The most logical next step is to start implementing the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's needed:\r\n1. First, I need to understand the pulse log format to build the classifier\r\n2. Then implement the actual classifier\r\n\r\nA concrete first action would be to create the TIC classifier script. Let me create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Extracts invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Classifies patterns\r\n\r\nOr I could create a specification document for the TIC implementation first.\r\n\r\nGiven the \"Be specific. Prefer file edits\" instruction, I should create an actual implementation file. Let me write a PowerShell script for the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what the TIC classifier needs to do:\r\n1. Load pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. Extract content sections (OBSERVATION, ACTION, MUTATION)\r\n3. Identify invariants (patterns that persist across pulses) vs variants (unique to each pulse)\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy\r\n5. Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nI'll create the TIC classifier script as a PowerShell file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant patterns (causal structure) vs variant content across pulse logs. The script needs to read pulse_*.md files, extract recurring vs unique patterns, and measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and implements next-pulse prediction, establishing the foundation for the empirical validation against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# TIC-EXPERIMENT.ps1 - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [int]$MinPulseCount = 5,\r\n    [float]$InvarianceThreshold = 0.6  # Pattern appears in X% of pulses = invariant\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 1: Load Pulse Logs ---\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n            Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -First 20\r\n    \r\n    $parsed = @()\r\n    foreach ($log in $logs) {\r\n        $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n        $parsed += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            File       = $log.Name\r\n            Raw        = $content\r\n            Observation = ([regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)### ACTION') | \r\n                         ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() })\r\n            Action     = ([regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)### MUTATION') | \r\n                         ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() })\r\n            Mutation   = ([regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)```\\s*\\nold_text:.*?new_text:.*?```') | \r\n                         ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[0].Value.Trim() })\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    return $parsed\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 2: Extract N-grams (tokenize) ---\r\nfunction Get-Ngrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 3)\r\n    \r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($Text, '\\b\\w+\\b') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.ToLower() }\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $tokens.Count - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngrams += ($tokens[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join ' ')\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 3: Classify Invariant vs Variant Patterns ---\r\nfunction Get-PatternClassification {\r\n    param($Pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Collect all ngrams across all pulses\r\n    $globalNgrams = @{}\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $Pulses) {\r\n        $allText = ($pulse.Observation + \" \" + $pulse.Action + \" \" + $pulse.Mutation)\r\n        $ngrams = Get-Ngrams -Text $allText -N 3\r\n        foreach ($ng in $ngrams) {\r\n            if ($globalNgrams.ContainsKey($ng)) {\r\n                $globalNgrams[$ng]++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $globalNgrams[$ng] = 1\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Classify: invariance_ratio = ngram_count / pulse_count\r\n    $pulseCount = $Pulses.Count\r\n    $invariants = @{}\r\n    $variants = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($ng in $globalNgrams.Keys) {\r\n        $ratio = $globalNgrams[$ng] / $pulseCount\r\n        if ($ratio -ge $InvarianceThreshold) {\r\n           \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:22:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355020935}}
